  "mixStrategy": "This Lo-Fi Hip Hop relaxation arrangement is built around a ii7\u2192V7\u2192Imaj7 then Imaj7\u2192vi7\u2192ii7\u2192V7 progression in F. The three tracks occupy distinct frequency bands to create a warm, spacious mix:\n\nBASS (Electric Bass, 100-300Hz, MIDI 29-45): Anchors the harmonic foundation with simple root notes and gentle chromatic walk-ups. Plays quarter/half note patterns locked to the chord changes. Sits at 0.7 volume to provide warmth without overwhelming. Rhythmically sparse \u2014 mostly roots on beat 1 with occasional 5ths as passing tones on beat 3.\n\nCHORDS (Warm Pad, 300Hz-2kHz, MIDI 48-67): Sustained 7th chord voicings that change with the progression. Open voicings (root-7th-3rd or 3rd-7th-root inversions) to avoid muddiness. Long sustains (3-6 seconds) create the dreamy, floating lo-fi atmosphere. Volume at 0.45 \u2014 felt more than heard, providing harmonic bed beneath the Rhodes.\n\nMELODY (Electric Piano/Rhodes, 1-8kHz, MIDI 65-79): The lead voice playing gentle jazz phrases \u2014 arpeggiated 7th chords, stepwise motion, and breathing space. Chord tones land on strong beats (1 and 3), with scale passing tones on weak beats. Slightly behind the beat feel achieved through gentle velocity swells. Volume at 0.6 \u2014 present but intimate.\n\nENERGY ARC: Segments 1-6 map across 45 seconds (~7.5s each). Energy starts sparse (0.3) with just bass and pad, builds melody in segment 2 (0.5), fills out in segments 3-4 (0.6-0.7 peak), then gently recedes in segments 5-6 (0.6\u21920.4). Note density and velocity both follow this arc. All tracks change chords simultaneously on the same beats, creating a unified band feel.\n\nCHORD MAP (at 61 BPM, quarter = ~0.984s, bar = ~3.93s):\nBars 1-2 (0-7.87s): Gm7 (ii7) \u2192 C7 (V7)\nBars 3-4 (7.87-15.74s): Fmaj7 (Imaj7) \u2192 Fmaj7\nBars 5-6 (15.74-23.61s): Dm7 (vi7) \u2192 Gm7 (ii7)\nBars 7-8 (23.61-31.48s): C7 (V7) \u2192 Fmaj7 (Imaj7)\nBars 9-10 (31.48-39.35s): Gm7 (ii7) \u2192 C7 (V7)\nBars 11-end (39.35-45s): Fmaj7 (Imaj7) \u2014 resolution and fade",
